(4) The office of a member of the Board shall become vacant— (a) upon his death; (b) if he is adjudicated a bankrupt or makes a composition with his creditors; (c) if he is absent from three consecutive meetings of the Board without special leave of the Board; (d) if he gives one month's notice in writing to the Minister of his intention to resign office and his resignation is accepted by the Minister; or (e) if his appointment is terminated by the Minister.
